main event: A radar detection of an unidentified flying object at Eglin AFB, Florida, in November 1957.
interesting points: The object was tracked on radar while maintaining an altitude of around 25,000 ft,The flight path of the tracked object was reported to be non-linear and in an arc pattern,Two separate objects were filtered through the radar system at intervals during a 30-minute observation period,The sighting included visual confirmations by military personnel despite the objects' fading from radar after reaching 22,000 ft altitude,The incident was classified as probably conventional unidentified due to various factors and experiences of radar operators.
sighted object: an unidentified flying object (UFO) detected on radar
witness description: military personnel involved in radar operations
